headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid TAP and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Even during a down period for the markets, Molson Coors has gone against the grain, climbing to $59.34. Its shares have yielded a 6% return over the last six months, beating the S&P 500 by 15.9%. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
